cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributed consensus protocols and their scalability issues. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to the communication flow in Paxos, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of PigPaxos on clusters of nodes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with fault-tolerance properties of distributed systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the communication bottleneck issue in distributed consensus protocols.
